5. **Streams not consumed/destroyed** — readable streams buffer in memory. Fix: always `.destroy()` or pipe to destination

**Debugging toolkit:**

```bash
# heap snapshot
node --inspect your-app.js
# then Chrome DevTools → Memory → Take Heap Snapshot

# track growth over time
node --expose-gc -e "
  setInterval(() => {
    global.gc();
    console.log(process.memoryUsage().heapUsed / 1024 / 1024, 'MB');
  }, 5000);
"
```

```js
